        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:46PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gerber Recreation Site, or 30 miles east of Klamath Falls, moving
northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gerber Recreation Site, Lorella, Barnes Valley At Gerber Resevoir,
and Bonanza.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
